  "text": "To quantify the effect of hydrocarbons on phase separation, the partitioning of the dyes over the L o and L d phases was used and reported as pL o /L d ratio. This ratio is equivalent to the partitioning coefficient (K p ) that was used by Levental and coworkers [CITATION_1] . A 5 pixel wide line was drawn through the middle of a GUV to avoid polarization effects, as shown in Figure 2 . The maxima of both peaks were determined and the pL o /L d was calculated. At least 50 GUVs per condition for each experiment were analysed.",
